The paper deals with supervised learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of self-information loss or log-loss indicates an information theoretic approach, which is a common theme in the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with individual data, which suggests a focus on personalized or individualized learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category. The mention of features and labels suggests a focus on classification or prediction tasks, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) possible sub-categories. Finally, the mention of training data and test data suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category as well.
